Moscow Region authorities spoke about the fate of closed landfills
Solid household waste landfills continue to be closed in the Moscow region.
This year, the authorities promise to eliminate the latter.
Some of the 39 landfills that existed in the region are being modernized into modern waste processing complexes.
But this option is not possible for every landfill - many of them have acquired dense residential development.
After the landfill is closed, it stands up for reclamation: the body of the landfill is covered with soil, degassing and infiltration systems are installed.
This makes it possible to stop chemical processes inside the landfill, so that it does not ignite, does not emit a stench, does not poison the soil and groundwater.
And then the former landfill is left to rise in a useless pile among the residential development surrounding it.
Why not make it something useful?
For example, in Ruza, where the reclamation of the "Annino" landfill was completed just a few days ago, the authorities are considering an option to make a ski slope out of a heap.
This landfill, which was in operation from 1976 to 2016, grew so that it went beyond the boundaries of the land allocated for it.
Therefore, during the reclamation, it was necessary to buy out neighboring areas, de facto long ago clogged with garbage.
"Some time will pass, the training ground will" sit down ," there will be fortresses, and we will think about what can be done to make it start to benefit.
A ski resort is striking, "the head of the Ruz district, Nikolai Parfenov, told reporters.
